explanation: This problem can be solved using dynamic programming. We maintain a 2D array dp where dp[i][j] represents the maximum score that can be achieved by selecting a contiguous subarray of length i and performing j operations. We iterate over all possible subarrays and update dp[i][j] by considering all possible previous subarrays and their scores. The gcd function is used to calculate the GCD of two numbers. The time complexity is O(n^3 * log(m)) due to the gcd function, where m is the maximum value in the array. The space complexity is O(n * k) for the dp array.

